---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Supervisor Development | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Brenkley Doctoral College's Supervisor Development programme — professional CPD for doctoral supervisors. £1,200 total. Recognised for CPD portfolios and institutional development.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Supervisor Development</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">Professional CPD for Doctoral Supervisors &mdash; £1,200 total</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">Doctoral supervision is a demanding and rewarding professional responsibility. Brenkley Doctoral College's Supervisor Development programme provides structured, evidence-based professional development for academics and professionals who are supervising, or preparing to supervise, doctoral researchers. Designed for supervisors at all experience levels.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">6 Months</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, online, with cohort learning elements</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£1,200</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Full programme fee. Group rates for institutional partners.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">CPD Recognised</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Suitable for inclusion in CPD portfolios and institutional staff development records</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Why This Programme</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Supervision Is a Skill</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Doctoral supervision is often treated as something that experienced academics simply absorb by doing. The evidence suggests otherwise. Effective supervision requires a specific set of skills — in feedback, in managing the supervisory relationship, in supporting researcher wellbeing, in navigating ethical complexity, and in understanding the particular demands of different kinds of doctoral research.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Many supervisors received little or no formal preparation for supervision. Brenkley Doctoral College's Supervisor Development programme provides that preparation — or, for experienced supervisors, an opportunity to reflect on, refine, and develop their practice through structured engagement with the evidence and with peers.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">The programme is of particular value to supervisors working with practitioner-researchers in professional doctorate or DBA programmes, where the distinctive dynamics of insider research and professional context create challenges that traditional academic supervision training does not address.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who Should Attend</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">For All Levels of Supervisory Experience</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">New Supervisors</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Academics or professionals taking on doctoral supervision for the first time, who want a structured foundation in supervisory practice before beginning.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Experienced Supervisors</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Supervisors with experience who want to reflect on and refine their practice, engage with current evidence on effective supervision, and address specific challenges they are encountering.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Institutional Teams</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Graduate schools, doctoral training partnerships, or HEI departments seeking a development programme for a cohort of supervisors. Group rates and in-house delivery available — contact us to discuss.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Industry Supervisors</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Industry or professional practitioners taking on a collaborative doctoral supervisory role and needing an introduction to the academic frameworks and responsibilities of supervision.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Programme Content -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Content</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Six Months of Structured Development</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Module 1: The Role of the Doctoral Supervisor</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">An evidence-based introduction to the supervisor role — the responsibilities, the boundaries, and the distinctive demands of supporting researchers to doctoral completion. Includes overview of UK Quality Code expectations and institutional frameworks.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Module 2: The Supervisory Relationship</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">What makes a supervisory relationship effective? This module examines the evidence on high-quality supervision, the dynamics of the supervisor-researcher relationship over time, and practical approaches to establishing a productive working relationship from the start.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Module 3: Supporting Research Quality</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">The academic heart of supervision — providing rigorous, developmental feedback on research writing, methodology, and argumentation. Includes structured practice with exemplar thesis chapters and peer feedback on supervisory practice.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Module 4: Wellbeing and Pastoral Responsibility</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Supervisors have a duty of care that extends beyond academic guidance. This module examines the pastoral dimension of supervision — recognising signs of researcher difficulty, supporting mental health and wellbeing, and knowing when and how to refer to specialist support.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Module 5: Supervising Practitioner-Researchers</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">The distinctive challenges and opportunities of supervising researchers who are conducting research in their own professional contexts. Covers insider positionality, ethics of organisational research, managing dual-role tensions, and making the most of practitioner-researcher access advantages.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Module 6: Supporting Completion and Examination Preparation</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">The final stages of the doctoral journey — thesis writing, pre-submission review, viva preparation, and post-viva revision. Includes guidance on the supervisor's role in the viva process and in supporting researchers through corrections.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 card">
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Cohort Learning</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm">The Supervisor Development programme runs in cohorts of up to twenty participants. Three live online seminars are included — one at the start, one midway through, and one at the end — providing opportunities for peer discussion, case-based learning, and facilitated reflection on supervisory practice. These sessions are led by Dr. Zahra Salimi and Dr. Liz Blower.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Institutional -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Institutional Partnerships</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Group and Institutional Rates</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Brenkley Doctoral College offers group rates for institutions enrolling three or more supervisors on the programme simultaneously. We can also deliver the programme in a bespoke in-house format for institutions wanting a tailored version for their own supervisory team.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Contact us at <a href="mailto:research@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">research@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a> with the subject line "Supervisor Development — Institutional Enquiry" to discuss group arrangements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Group Pricing</h3>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
            <div class="flex justify-between"><span>1–2 participants</span><span class="font-medium text-foreground">£1,200 per person</span></div>
            <div class="flex justify-between"><span>3–5 participants</span><span class="font-medium text-foreground">£1,050 per person</span></div>
            <div class="flex justify-between"><span>6–10 participants</span><span class="font-medium text-foreground">£950 per person</span></div>
            <div class="flex justify-between"><span>10+ participants</span><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Contact us for pricing</span></div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-3">Bespoke in-house delivery available. Pricing on application.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Invest in your supervisory practice</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Good supervision changes lives. The next cohort of the Brenkley Doctoral College Supervisor Development programme starts in September 2026. Enrolment is now open.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Enrol now</a>
        <a href="/fees" class="btn-outline">Fee information</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
